# Set Matrix Zeroes

This is the solution to the problem of setting entire rows and columns of a matrix to zeroes if an element is `0`. This problem is typically asked in technical interviews and is a common problem in coding assessments.

### Problem Statement:

Given an `m x n` matrix, if an element in the matrix is `0`, set its entire row and column to `0`. Do it in place (without using extra space).

### Approach:

We can solve this problem efficiently using constant space. Here's how we can do that:

- Use the first row and first column of the matrix to mark which rows and columns need to be set to zero.
- Use two variables to track whether the first row and the first column themselves need to be zeroed.

### Code:

```cpp
#include <vector>
using namespace std;

class Solution {
public:
    void setZeroes(vector<vector<int>>& matrix) {
        int n = matrix.size();        
        int m = matrix[0].size();      
        bool firstrowzero = false;     
        bool firstcolzero = false;     

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (matrix[i][0] == 0) {
                firstcolzero = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
            if (matrix[0][i] == 0) {
                firstrowzero = true;
                break;
            }
        }

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = 1; j < m; j++) {
                if (matrix[i][j] == 0) {
                    matrix[0][j] = 0; // Mark the first row
                    matrix[i][0] = 0; // Mark the first column
                }
            }
        }

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            if (matrix[i][0] == 0) {
                for (int j = 0; j < m; j++) {
                    matrix[i][j] = 0;
                }
            }
        }

        for (int i = 1; i < m; i++) {
            if (matrix[0][i] == 0) {
                for (int j = 0; j < n; j++) {
                    matrix[j][i] = 0;
                }
            }
        }

        if (firstrowzero) {
            for (int i = 0; i < m; i++) {
                matrix[0][i] = 0;
            }
        }

        if (firstcolzero) {
            for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
                matrix[i][0] = 0;
            }
        }
    }
};
